default Statistical significance is a way of estimating the likelihood that a difference between two samples indicates a rea
defaultl difference between populations from which the samples are taken, rather than being due to chance. 
defaultThe significance level is set at 0.05, which means that there is only a 5% chance that the difference in results is due to chance.
